# A&R — Smart Money sync (13F superinvestors)
# Install with: crontab -e   (then paste the lines below)
# View logs:    tail -f ~/Library/Logs/ayr-sync-funds.log
#
# Schedule rationale:
#   - 13F filings are due 45 days after quarter end:
#       Q4 -> Feb 14   |   Q1 -> May 15   |   Q2 -> Aug 14   |   Q3 -> Nov 14
#     So days 15/16/17 are when funds actually publish. Run at 09:00 local
#     three days in a row to catch late filers and any FMP ingestion lag.
#   - Day 1 is a light monthly sweep (cheap insurance for backfills).
#   - Day 20 covers Spanish semestrales (Cobas / Magallanes / azValor), which
#     are filed mid-Feb and mid-Aug; the 20th gives the CNMV pipeline time
#     to settle and also serves as a second monthly safety net.

# 13F primary window — days 15, 16, 17 of every month at 09:00 local time
0 9 15,16,17 * * /Users/ricardogarciaontoso/IA/AyR/scripts/sync-funds.sh

# Monthly safety pass — day 1 at 09:00 (catches any late-filer backfill)
0 9 1 * *      /Users/ricardogarciaontoso/IA/AyR/scripts/sync-funds.sh

# Spanish semestrales + second safety pass — day 20 at 09:00
0 9 20 * *     /Users/ricardogarciaontoso/IA/AyR/scripts/sync-funds.sh
